South Carolina Bar
June 25 at 11:55 AM ¬∑

The Law Related Education (LRE) Division has announced the winners of the 2020 LRE awards. The results are below. Congratulations, everyone!

High School Mock Trial Scholarship recipients:
Nick Adamo, Heathwood Hall Episcopal School;
Grace Brackett, Wade Hampton High School;
Salomon Campos-Rice, Wilson High School;
Lauren Chen, Dutch Fork High School;
Gene Gubatina, Carolina Forest High School;
Derek Rhodes, Strom Thurmond High School;
Anthony Scott, Strom Thurmond High School;
Michael Wood, Strom Thurmond High School

We the People Scholarship recipient:
Gene Gubatina, Carolina Forest High School

Middle School Teacher of the Year:
Lakena Ackerman, Southeast Middle School, Richland County School District One

High School Teacher of the Year:
Gary Salazar, South Carolina Governor's School for Science and Mathematics

LRE Lawyer of the Year:
Bianca Williams

LRE Legacy Award:
Brantley Brinkley

